6. Better Approach (Incremental Recursion)

Idea

Instead of storing every subset and calculating its sum repeatedly, keep a running sum while making recursive calls.

Each recursive call decides:

Take current element.

Skip current element.


This avoids recalculating subset sums.


---

Algorithm

Function(index, currentSum, taken)

If index == n

    return taken AND currentSum % k == 0

Take current element

Don't take current element

Return OR of both answers


---

Code (Python)

class Solution:
    def subsetSumDivisible(self, arr, k):
        n = len(arr)

        def dfs(index, curr_sum, taken):
            if index == n:
                return taken and curr_sum % k == 0

            if dfs(index + 1, curr_sum + arr[index], True):
                return True

            return dfs(index + 1, curr_sum, taken)

        return dfs(0, 0, False)


