9. Why This Works

Suppose a subset has sum

S

Only

S % k

matters.

Whenever we add a new number

num

new remainder becomes

(S % k + num % k) % k

which is equivalent to

(S + num) % k

Thus, by tracking only remainders, we correctly represent all possible subset sums without storing the actual sums.


